### QUICK REFERENCE - Common Test Scenarios

### ==========================================
### 1. TEST ALL SCENARIOS - QUICK RUN
### ==========================================

### 1.1 Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 1.2 Register New Tenant
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test Tenant",
  "phone": "0812345678",
  "email": "tenant@quicktest.com",
  "password": "TestPassword123",
  "role": "TENANT"
}

### 1.3 Login and Capture Token
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "tenant@quicktest.com",
  "password": "TestPassword123"
}

@token = {{response.body.data.access_token}}

### 1.4 Try ADMIN-Only Endpoint with Tenant Token (Will Fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/create
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "New User",
  "phone": "0899999999",
  "email": "newuser@quicktest.com",
  "password": "Password123",
  "role": "TENANT"
}

### 1.5 Try ADMIN-Only Endpoint without Token (Will Fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/create
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "New User",
  "phone": "0899999999",
  "email": "newuser2@quicktest.com",
  "password": "Password123",
  "role": "TENANT"
}

### ==========================================
### 2. AUTHENTICATION FLOW SIMPLIFIED
### ==========================================

### 2.1 Register
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "User Name",
  "phone": "0812345678",
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "Password123",
  "role": "TENANT"
}

### 2.2 Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "Password123"
}

### ==========================================
### 3. ERROR SCENARIOS
### ==========================================

### 3.1 Register with Duplicate Email
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Another User",
  "phone": "0812345678",
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "Password123",
  "role": "TENANT"
}

### 3.2 Register as ADMIN (Blocked)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Admin User",
  "phone": "0812345678",
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "AdminPassword",
  "role": "ADMIN"
}

### 3.3 Login with Wrong Password
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "WrongPassword"
}

### 3.4 Access Protected Route without Token
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/create
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "New User",
  "phone": "0899999999",
  "email": "newuser@example.com",
  "password": "Password123",
  "role": "TENANT"
}

### 3.5 Access Protected Route with Invalid Token
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/create
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer invalid.token.string

{
  "name": "New User",
  "phone": "0899999999",
  "email": "newuser@example.com",
  "password": "Password123",
  "role": "TENANT"
}

### ==========================================
### 4. ROLE-BASED ACCESS CONTROL CHECK
### ==========================================
### After successful login, use token in Authorization header

### Admin Can: Create & Delete Users
### Tenant Cannot: Create & Delete Users

### 4.1 Create User (Requires ADMIN)
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/create
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "name": "New User",
  "phone": "0899999999",
  "email": "newuser@example.com",
  "password": "Password123",
  "role": "TENANT"
}

### 4.2 Delete User (Requires ADMIN)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/user/12345-67890-uuid
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### ==========================================
### NOTES
### ==========================================
### - Replace {{baseUrl}} with actual server URL
### - Replace {{token}} with actual JWT token from login response
### - Replace {{adminToken}} with actual ADMIN JWT token
### - Expected Status Codes:
###   - 200/201/202: Success
###   - 400: Bad Request (validation error)
###   - 401: Unauthorized (missing/invalid token, or role mismatch)
###   - 403: Forbidden (insufficient permissions)
### - All tokens expire (check JWT configuration for duration)
### - All emails must be unique
### - All required fields must be present in requests
